<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="503" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1535,1994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,258,1535,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Saperdini">Saperdini</taxonomicName>
is one of the most diverse tribes in 
<taxonomicName box="[652,814,1535,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1825" box="[828,940,1535,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lamiinae">Lamiinae</taxonomicName>
), with 155 genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H." pageId="12" pageNumber="503" refId="ref10996" refString="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2018) Titan, base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 29 January 2019)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramirez Hernandez, J. J. &amp; Santos-Silva, A. &amp; Nascimento, F. E. L." box="[339,702,1571,1598]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" pagination="87 - 99" refId="ref10925" refString="Ramirez Hernandez, J. J., Santos-Silva, A. &amp; Nascimento, F. E. L. (2019) New species, new genera, and new records in Cerambycidae from Peru (Coleoptera). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, New Series, 55 (1), 87 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2018.1556118" type="journal article" year="2019">
Ramírez Hernández 
<emphasis box="[567,622,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis box="[820,1072,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Hemilocallia grishami</emphasis>
based on a single male specimen collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[288,339,1608,1634]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Peru</collectingCountry>
(see photograph of the 
<typeStatus box="[605,703,1607,1633]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">holotype</typeStatus>
at 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezark, L. G." box="[737,884,1607,1634]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" refId="ref10202" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2019) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available from: https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n (accessed January 2019)" type="url" year="2019">Bezark 2019</bibRefCitation>
). A few days after publication, our friend Herbert Schmid (City, 
<collectingCountry box="[313,399,1643,1670]" name="Austria" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Austria</collectingCountry>
?) alerted us to the synonymy between this species and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[1020,1304,1644,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Glenea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata" subGenus="Glenea">
<emphasis box="[1020,1101,1644,1670]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Glenea</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1118,1199,1644,1670]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Glenea</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1215,1304,1644,1670]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an African species. Accordingly, 
<emphasis box="[399,545,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Hemilocallia</emphasis>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Glenea)" box="[817,1007,1680,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Glenea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Glenea">
<emphasis box="[817,898,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Glenea</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[915,996,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Glenea</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis box="[1069,1204,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">H. grishami</emphasis>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[182,358,1716,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Glenea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata" subGenus="Glenea">
<emphasis box="[182,209,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">G.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[225,252,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">G.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[269,358,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1535,1994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">
It is important to mention that all American 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1839" box="[714,821,1751,1777]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Saperdini">Saperdini</taxonomicName>
have the claws simple and divaricate (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsley, E. G. &amp; Chemsak, J. A." pageId="12" pageNumber="503" refId="ref10632" refString="Linsley, E. G. &amp; Chemsak, J. A. (1985) The Cerambycidae of North America. Part VII. No. 1. Taxonomy and classification of the subfamily Lamiinae, tribes Parmenini through Acanthoderini. University of California, Publications in Entomology 102. University of California, Berkeley, xi + 258 pp." type="book" year="1985">Linsley &amp; Chemsak 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsley, E. G. &amp; Chemsak, J. A." box="[333,393,1787,1814]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" refId="ref10694" refString="Linsley, E. G. &amp; Chemsak, J. A. (1995) The Cerambycidae of North America. Part VII. No. 2. Taxonomy and classification of the subfamily Lamiinae, tribes Acanthocinini through Hemilophini. University of California, Publications in Entomology 114. University of California, Berkeley, xii + 292 pp." type="book" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
). However, several non-American species, belonging to several genera, have the tarsal claws bifid or appendiculate, at least in males. Although it is usually mentioned in the literature that only the male’s foreleg claws of some species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Newman, 1842" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" box="[438,698,1860,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Glenea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[438,519,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Glenea</emphasis>
Newman, 1842
</taxonomicName>
have the tarsal claws modified, males of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[1164,1341,1860,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Glenea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata" subGenus="Glenea">
<emphasis box="[1164,1192,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">G.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1208,1236,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">G.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1252,1341,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have all tarsal claws appendiculate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="503" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1535,1994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">
Since only a single specimen was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[713,767,1932,1958]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">Peru</collectingCountry>
, we do not know if the species is established in that country. For a complete list of references on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[555,731,1968,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Glenea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata" subGenus="Glenea">
<emphasis box="[555,582,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">G.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[598,626,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">G.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[642,731,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="503">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H." box="[787,1150,1967,1994]" pageId="12" pageNumber="503" refId="ref10996" refString="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2018) Titan, base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 29 January 2019)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte (2018)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
